What is the quotient when $8x^3+16x^2-7x+4$ is divided by $2x+5$?
inference:
$$8x^3+16x^2-7x+4\div\div2x+5$$ 
Dividing the first by the second:
$$=(8x^3+16x^2-7x+4)\div\div(2x+5)=\frac{8x^3+16x^2-7x+4}{2x+5}$$
Factoring the numerator
$$=\frac{8x^3+16x^2-7x+4}{2x+5}=\frac{(8x^3+16x^2)-(7x+4)}{2x+5}=\frac{8x^2(x+2)-7(x+2)}{2x+5}$$
Taking $(x+2)$ common from the numerator
$$=\frac{(8x^2-7)(x+2)}{2x+5}=\frac{8x^2-7}{2x+5}(x+2)$$
Final Answer: \boxed{4x^2-3x+2} I hope it is correct.
